ClockNodes.Name: HSCLK
ClockNodes.Signpost: To use this oscillator, please select the HSCLK HIGH SPEED OSCILLATOR in one of the clock source multiplexers.

ClockNodes.Name: LPCLK
ClockNodes.Signpost: To use this oscillator, please select the LPCLK LOW POWER OSCILLATOR in one of the clock source multiplexers.

ClockNodes.Name: INRO
ClockNodes.Signpost: To use this oscillator, please select the INRO in one of the clock source multiplexers.

ClockNodes.Name: APBCLK
ClockNodes.Signpost: This divider has a fixed divisor of 2 and cannot be configured.

ClockNodes.Name: AHBCLK
ClockNodes.Signpost: On MAX32650, the AHB CLK runs at the same frequency as the System Clock, so no clock divider is used.

ClockNodes.Name: USB_CLK_DIV_4
ClockNodes.Signpost: This divider has a fixed divisor of 4 and cannot be configured.

ClockNodes.Name: 32KIN
ClockNodes.Signpost: The 32KIN pin should be connected to an external clock source and cannot be configured.

ClockNodes.Name: 32KOUT
ClockNodes.Signpost: The 32KOUT pin receives the output from the ERTCO and cannot be configured.

ClockNodes.Name: WDT0/1
ClockNodes.Signpost: The Watchdog Timers are always active and cannot be disabled.

ClockNodes.Name: Cortex-M4
ClockNodes.Signpost: To set up the clock for the Cortex-M4, please configure the multiplexers and dividers on the canvas.

ClockNodes.Name: ERTCO
ClockNodes.Signpost: Use of the ERTCO may be controlled by configuring the ERTCO Bypass multiplexer on the canvas.

ClockNodes.Name: 7MCLK
ClockNodes.Signpost: To use this oscillator, please select the 7MCLK OSCILLATOR & BAUD RATE CLOCK in one of the clock source multiplexers.

ClockNodes.Name: FLC
ClockNodes.Signpost: The dividers for the flash controller is set automatically by the driver code.

ClockNodes.Name: POWER SEQ
ClockNodes.Signpost: The Power Sequencer is always active and cannot be disabled.

Fields.Name: READY
Fields.Documentation: Cleared by hardware when at any time the cache as a whole is invalidated (including a system reset). When this bit is 0, the cache is effectively in bypass mode (instruction fetches will come from main memory or from the line fill buffer). Set by hardware when the invalidate operation is complete and the cache is ready.

Fields.Name: ACCESS_FAIL

Fields.Name: SDHCFRQ
Fields.Description: This Bit Selects the Frequency of the SDHC Clock
Fields.Documentation: If set, the clock oscillates at 50Mhz, otherwise it will oscillate at 60MHz.

Enum.Name: 50M
Enum.Documentation: SDHC Freq = 50Mhz.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.

Registers.Documentation: Each bit controls the GPIO_EN setting for one GPIO pin on the associated port. These bits configure the corresponding device pin for digital I/O or an alternate function mode. The fields can be modified directly by writing to this register or indirectly through GPIOn_EN0_SET or GPIOn_EN0_CLR.
